description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your Community Hospital Needs You Now More Than Ever - this is &lt;em&gt;YOUR&lt;/em&gt; time to care!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Flexible &amp; Bespoke Rotational Posts Across a Variety of Specialties are Available Immediately at Award Winning Haywood Hospital for all Registered Nurses &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;We aim to interview and provide a job offer to successful candidates with 48 hours of receiving your application &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Whether you&#39;re simply looking for a change, have a &lt;strong&gt;few additional hours to spare&lt;/strong&gt;or you have recently retired but would like to return to practice to support the NHS during these challenging times, we can offer you &lt;strong&gt;flexible hours, flexible contracts and a supportive environment&lt;/strong&gt; in which our wonderful nurses have &lt;strong&gt;the&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;time to care.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Haywood Community Hospital is situated in Burslem, Stoke-On-Trent and provides a &lt;strong&gt;whole range of services&lt;/strong&gt; including specialist in-patient and out-patient rehabilitation services, multi-professional in-patient wards, a Walk-in Centre, Therapies, Limb Fitting Service and a wide range of Rheumatology services (out-patient and day case). All of our wards are Dementia Friendly and the admission age range is 18 years onwards. The 6 C principles are embedded in all we do: &lt;strong&gt;Care * Compassion * Competence * Communication * Courage * Commitment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Many of our services are world &lt;strong&gt;renowned for excellence&lt;/strong&gt; and we are very proud to have recently achieved the &lt;strong&gt;Gold Service User Award&lt;/strong&gt; as well as being &lt;strong&gt;commended for our work with Student Nurses.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you share our values, please contact us now – &lt;strong&gt;we will fast track your application to enable you to join our team as soon as possible&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information and to arrange your interview via MS Teams, please contact our Recruitment &amp; Resourcing Manager via &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;martine.stokes@mpft.nhs.uk &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust actively encourages applications from members of our Black, Asian and Minority Ethnic communities it’s important to us that our workforce reflects the diversity of our communities as much as possible.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Part time, job share and flexible working applications will be considered and supported, where possible. We are a Disability Confident Employer applicants who declare a disability and meet the essential criteria in the job description will be invited to interview.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
